  "response_text": "For a healthy and delicious celebration dinner, consider the following menu:\n\n**Main Course:**\nGrilled Salmon with Lemon and Herbs: Salmon is a great source of omega-3 fatty acids, protein, and various vitamins and minerals. Pair it with a squeeze of fresh lemon juice and a sprinkle of chopped herbs like parsley, dill, or thyme.\n\n**Sides:**\n1. Roasted Vegetables: Roast a variety of colorful vegetables like Brussels sprouts, bell peppers, carrots, and zucchini with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper.\n2. Quinoa and Black Bean Salad: Mix cooked quinoa with cooked black beans, diced tomatoes, chopped cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice.\n3. Grilled Asparagus: Brush asparagus spears with olive oil and grill them until tender, seasoning with salt, pepper, and a sprinkle of parmesan cheese.\n\n**Dessert:**\nFresh Fruit Tart: Create a tart with a whole-wheat crust, topped with a mixture of fresh berries like strawberries, blueberries, and raspberries. You can also add a dollop of Greek yogurt or a sprinkle of dark chocolate shavings for extra flavor.\n\n**Beverage:**\n1. Sparkling Water with Lemon and Mint: Add slices of lemon and a few sprigs of fresh mint to a pitcher of sparkling water for a refreshing and healthy drink.\n2. Red Wine (optional): If you prefer a celebratory drink, consider a glass of red wine, which contains antioxidants and may have health benefits when consumed in moderation.\n\nThis menu offers a balanced and nutritious dinner that's perfect for a celebration, with a focus on whole foods, lean protein, and plenty of fruits and vegetables. Enjoy your special occasion!",
